Direct Known Subclasses:
HeavyWeightVertex, WorldVertex
public class Vertex extends GraphNode
A vertex in a Graph, representing one end of an Edge (either the "from" vertex or the "to" vertex), and possibly defining an intersection with other edges if the vertex is not a dead-end.

Note that a Graph API Vertex is NOT ALWAYS a map node as Graph API Vertexes only occur at Edge end-points (as opposed to map nodes which are defined for every shape point of every way). You can also get all the shape points along an Edge via Edge.shapePoints().

Note that a Vertex is a small "flyweight" object, having only three fields: a Graph reference, an integer vertex identifier and a cached integer index. All other attributes are stored in a compressed form in the graph's GraphStore implementation. This makes it very efficient for Java to work with large numbers of Vertexes.

Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
